<p>I want To Store Data By Component</p>  <p><strong>My Component Name UpdatedateComponent</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php class UpdatedateComponent extends Component     {            public function clean($string)             {                 $string = str_replace(' ', '-', $string); // Replaces all spaces with hyphens.                 return preg_replace('/[^A-Za-z0-9\-]/', '', $string); // Removes special chars.             }          public function updatedatefunction($proid,$edit,$model1,$model2,$field)             {                 if ($this-&gt;request-&gt;is(array('post', 'put'))) {                     $this-&gt;$model1-&gt;$model2-&gt;id = $edit;                     $this-&gt;request-&gt;data[$model2][$field] = $proid;                     date_default_timezone_set('Asia/Kolkata');                     $date = date('Y/m/d H:i:s');                     $this-&gt;request-&gt;data[$model2]['cganges'] = $date;                     $this-&gt;$model1-&gt;$model2-&gt;save($this-&gt;request-&gt;data);                 }              }     } ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I want To store Data From <code>SlidermasterControler</code></p>  <pre><code>$this-&gt;Updatedate-&gt;updatedatefunction($proid,1,'Slidermaster','Homesliderchangemaster','slidermaster_id'); </code></pre>